During the six-week shutdown, an expert operational team tends to all its needs. CAPE TOWN - The Mother City's iconic cableway has for nearly a century been creating memorable moments for tourists and locals alike. But a lot of care goes into keeping the ride in tip-top shape. During the six-week shutdown, an expert operational team tends to all its needs, including walking a thin line to replace cable car ropes. Maintenance was set to continue for another week. But progress was such that Table Mountain lovers are already able to return.